y_id></item><item><title>Golf Heads to Big 12 Championship</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/26/golf-heads-to-big-12-championship</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/26/golf-heads-to-big-12-championship</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Big 12 Championship" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/26/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_Big12C.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University golf team will compete in the Big 12 Golf Championship from Monday to Wednesday in Hutchinson, Kansas.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/26/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_Big12C.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/26/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_Big12C.jpg"><media:title>Big 12 Championship</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/26/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_Big12C.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 11:02:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59046</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Win Conclusion of Friday's Game, Drop Second Game</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/25/baseball-mountaineers-win-conclusion-of-fridays-game-drop-second-game</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/25/baseball-mountaineers-win-conclusion-of-fridays-game-drop-second-game</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxwell Molessa swings and hits a go-ahead two-run single in the 13th inning against Cincinnati" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/25/DSC04920.jpg" /><br /><br />CINCINNATI (April 25, 2026) – Picking up in the 12th inning of a 5-5 game, the No. 12 West Virginia University baseball team scored four in the 13th to win the conclusion of the suspended game, 9-5, over Cincinnati. In the regularly scheduled contest, the Mountaineers fell to the Bearcats, 5-2, Saturday afternoon at UC Baseball Stadium.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/25/DSC04920.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/25/DSC04920.jpg"><media:title>Maxwell Molessa swings and hits a go-ahead two-run single in the 13th inning against Cincinnati</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/25/DSC04920.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 25 Apr 2026 20:42:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59045</s:story_id></item><item><title>Take your Graduation Photos at Milan Puskar Stadium</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/22/general-take-your-graduation-photos-at-milan-puskar-stadium</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/22/general-take-your-graduation-photos-at-milan-puskar-stadium</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Graduation photos are being offered at Milan Puskar Stadium in May 2026 at certain rates." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/20/WVU26_GradPhotosAtMPS_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/WVU26_GradPhotosAtMPS_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/WVU26_GradPhotosAtMPS_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>Graduation photos are being offered at Milan Puskar Stadium in May 2026 at certain rates.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/20/WVU26_GradPhotosAtMPS_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 11:07:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59033</s:story_id></item><item><title>Game Against Cincinnati Suspended in 12th Inning</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/24/baseball-game-against-cincinnati-suspended-in-12th-inning</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/24/baseball-game-against-cincinnati-suspended-in-12th-inning</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Ryan Maggy fist bumps first base coach Jacob Garcia after hitting a single." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/24/DSC04200.jpg" /><br /><br />CINCINNATI – Friday night's baseball game between No. 12 West Virginia and Cincinnati has been suspended due to rain in the bottom of the 12th inning with the score tied, 5-5. The game will resume on Saturday at 3 p.m., followed by the regularly scheduled game.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/24/DSC04200.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/24/DSC04200.jpg"><media:title>Ryan Maggy fist bumps first base coach Jacob Garcia after hitting a single.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/24/DSC04200.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 21:41:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59044</s:story_id></item><item><title>Judis Finishes Eighth in 10,000m at Penn Relays</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/24/track-field-judis-finishes-eighth-in-10-000m-at-penn-relays</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/24/track-field-judis-finishes-eighth-in-10-000m-at-penn-relays</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chiara Judis" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/24/chiarajudis.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia's Chiara Judis competed in the 10,000 meters at the Penn Relays on Thursday night.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/24/chiarajudis.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/24/chiarajudis.jpg"><media:title>Chiara Judis</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/24/chiarajudis.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 01:07:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59043</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kellogg Announces Signing of Khyala Ngodu</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/23/womens-basketball-kellogg-announces-signing-of-khyala-ngodu</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/23/womens-basketball-kellogg-announces-signing-of-khyala-ngodu</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WBB Hope Coliseum" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/6/WBB_Stadium_Photo__8_.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University women's basketball head coach Mark Kellogg has announced the addition of Khyala Ngodu (Fort Lauderdale, Fla. / UCF / Dillard High School) to a grant-in-aid for the 2026-27 academic year.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/6/WBB_Stadium_Photo__8_.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/6/WBB_Stadium_Photo__8_.jpg"><media:title>WBB Hope Coliseum</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/6/WBB_Stadium_Photo__8_.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 13:48:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59037</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Head to Cincinnati for Weekend Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/23/baseball-mountaineers-head-to-cincinnati-for-weekend-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/23/baseball-mountaineers-head-to-cincinnati-for-weekend-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup vs. Cincinnati" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/23/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Cincy.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 12 West Virginia University baseball team travels to Cincinnati for a Big 12 series, April 24-26. First pitch on Friday is set for 6 p.m. ET, Saturday for 3 p.m. ET, and Sunday for 1 p.m. ET.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/23/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Cincy.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/23/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Cincy.jpg"><media:title>Matchup vs. Cincinnati</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/23/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Cincy.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 11:41:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59042</s:story_id></item><item><title>Rowing Set for Lake Wheeler Invitational</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/23/rowing-set-for-lake-wheeler-invitational</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/23/rowing-set-for-lake-wheeler-invitational</guid><category>Rowing</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Lake Wheeler Invitational" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/23/ROW26_RaceDayLWI_1920X1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University rowing team travels to Raleigh, North Carolina, on April 24-25, for the Lake Wheeler Invitational.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/23/ROW26_RaceDayLWI_1920X1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/23/ROW26_RaceDayLWI_1920X1080.jpg"><media:title>Lake Wheeler Invitational</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/23/ROW26_RaceDayLWI_1920X1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 11:36:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>12</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59041</s:story_id></item><item><title>Bassinger, Perez Named to Stopper of the Year Watch List</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/22/baseball-bassinger-perez-named-to-stopper-of-the-year-watch-list</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/22/baseball-bassinger-perez-named-to-stopper-of-the-year-watch-list</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Reese Bassinger, David Perez" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/22/EKQ06498_large.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University pitchers Reese Bassinger and David Perez have been named to the National Collegiate Baseball Writers Association (NCBWA) Stopper of the Year Midseason Watch List, two of 61 players across Division I.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/22/EKQ06498_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/22/EKQ06498_large.jpg"><media:title>Reese Bassinger, David Perez</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/22/EKQ06498_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 15:31:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59039</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>